    "notes": "Detection should focus on network discovery binaries (ipconfig.exe, arp.exe, route.exe) spawned by processes in user-writable paths (AppData\\Local\\Temp). The parent process path C:\\Users\\dkim\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\svc_updater.exe is a high-fidelity indicator. Benign events share the same child process name but have legitimate parents (interactive cmd.exe or known IT tooling). A compound rule requiring BOTH the child binary being a network enum tool AND the parent living in a temp/user-writable path will sharply reduce FPs while maintaining TP coverage."
